    Sense disambiguation is also necessary for certain syntactic analyses, such as prepositional phrase attachment (Jensen and Binot 1987; Whittemore, Ferrara, and Brunner 1990; Hindle and Rooth 1993), and, in general, restricts the space of competing parses (Alshawi and Carter 1994).
    The problem of word sense disambiguation (WSD) has been described as &amp;quot;AI-complete,&amp;quot; that is, a problem which can be solved only by first resolving all the difficult problems in artificial intelligence (Al), such as the representation of common sense and encyclopedic knowledge.
